<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Three-time Grammy winner Kelly Clarkson touched on her impending divorce from manager Brandon Blackstock, whom she legally separated from on June 4, while appearing on Sunday TODAY.</p>

<p>'I mean, it's no secret. My life has been a little bit of a dumpster,' the 38-year-old Texan pop powerhouse admitted to host Willie Geist.</p>

<p>'Personally, it's been a little hard the last couple months. I've been talking to friends that have been through divorce. I don't know how people go through that without having some kind of outlet because it is the worst thing ever for everyone involved.' </p>

<p>End of an era: Three-time Grammy winner Kelly Clarkson touched on her impending divorce from manager Brandon Blackstock (L), whom she legally separated from on June 4, while appearing on Sunday TODAY</p>

<p>The 38-year-old Texan pop powerhouse admitted to host Willie Geist: 'I mean, it's no secret. My life has been a little bit of a dumpster. Personally, it's been a little hard the last couple months'</p>

<p>After nearly seven years of marriage, Kelly is now requesting joint legal and physical custody of her son Remington, 4; and daughter River, 6; with the 43-year-old former stepson of Reba McEntire.</p>

<p>However, Clarkson did not request custody of Brandon's two older children - daughter Savannah, 18; and son Seth, 13 - from his first marriage to Melissa Ashworth.</p>

<p>'This next record will probably be the most personal one I've ever released,' the I Dare You songstress said.</p>

<p>'And the whole record is basically every emotion you experience from the beginning of a relationship to the end of what it is now or where it is now, and it's been very therapeutic for me.'   </p>

<p>Kelly continued: 'I've been talking to friends that have been through divorce. I don't know how people go through that without having some kind of outlet because it is the worst thing ever for everyone involved'</p>

<p>'Irreconcilable differences': After nearly seven years of marriage, Clarkson is now requesting joint legal and physical custody of her daughter River, 6; and son Remington, 4; with the 43-year-old former stepson of Reba McEntire (pictured in 2018) </p>

<p>Stepchildren: However, the I Dare You songstress did not request custody of Brandon's two older children - daughter Savannah, 18; and son Seth, 13 - from his first marriage to Melissa Ashworth (pictured April 27)</p>

<p>Kelly finds it 'weird' that her kids sing one of the tracks she's working on while in the car: 'I've never written about my life to where my kids are, like, singing along.'</p>

<p>Clarkson impressively scored a Daytime Emmy Award for outstanding entertainment host for the inaugural season of her talk show The Kelly Clarkson Show, which returns for season two on September 21.</p>

<p>'I've been covering songs for almost 20 years now on tour. I choose all the songs from all the ones that fans send in,' the original American Idol champ said of her popular 'Kellyoke' segments.</p>

<p>'I don't know until the morning of and then I just listen to it before I got out. I'm so used to covering songs. It's so innate in me to try to do something different.' </p>

<p>Kelly said: 'This next record will probably be the most personal one I've ever released. And the whole record is basically every emotion you experience from the beginning of a relationship to the end of what it is now or where it is now, and it's been very therapeutic for me'</p>

